Parameter.Name: CmeTradeMessageProcessing
Parameter.Comment: 0 = USE_M6_ONLY, 1 = USE_M0_ONLY, 2 = USE_M0_AND_M6_FOR_VOLUME

Parameter.Name: PublishConsolidatedTrades
Parameter.Comment: All CME updates are "consolidated".

Parameter.Name: CmeProcessExPitTrades
Parameter.Comment: Whether to request process ex-pit trades received on the M6 messages

Parameter.Name: CmeExPitTradesIrreg
Parameter.Comment: Ex-pit trades are treated as irregular by default i.e. the prices and volumes are published as irregular so they do not contribute to the total value, total volume or vwap. When this parameter is set to false ex-pit prices and quantities are published to non-irregular fields, affecting the total value and total volume, and triggering updates to the vwap

Parameter.Name: CmeUseCmeInstrumentGroupForGroupMaps
Parameter.Comment: Controls whether to use CME Instrument Group Code or first two letter of the symbol for Group Maps.

Parameter.Name: CmeUseContractChannelMapForMO
Parameter.Comment: This parameter is used together with the contract channel map configurations found in the file cmemdp_contract_channels.xml. Simply include the varying parameter groups into the various cmemdp_rlc feed configurations found later in the cmemdp.xml file. So for instance in the cmemdp_rlc_7 feed stanza you would put a UseParameterGroup name=CmeMdpContractChannel7 line. You would also need to change CmeUseContractChannelMapForMO to true. Doing this should save you some memory by filtering out MO messages for contracts that you don't want on the feed you are running.

Parameter.Name: CmeUpdateStatusOnMjTypeP
Parameter.Comment: Security Status is set upon receipt of some of the MJ messages. The MJ messages are sent for the entire product group. So receipt of a single MJ message triggers a roll for all instruments in that product group. In some cases the MJ messages can come in rapid succession and can cause high update rates. Some clients are not very interested in these Security Status updates as well. Changing this parameter to false turns off the security status update for this MJ Type.

Parameter.Name: CmeUpdateStatusOnMjTypeO
Parameter.Comment: Security Status is set upon receipt of some of the MJ messages. The MJ messages are sent for the entire product group. So receipt of a single MJ message triggers a roll for all instruments in that product group. In some cases the MJ messages can come in rapid succession and can cause high update rates. Some clients are not very interested in these Security Status updates as well. Changing this parameter to false turns off the security status update for this MJ Type.

Parameter.Name: CmeUpdateStatusOnMjTypeS
Parameter.Comment: Security Status is set upon receipt of some of the MJ messages. The MJ messages are sent for the entire product group. So receipt of a single MJ message triggers a roll for all instruments in that product group. In some cases the MJ messages can come in rapid succession and can cause high update rates. Some clients are not very interested in these Security Status updates as well. Changing this parameter to false turns off the security status update for this MJ Type.

Parameter.Name: CmeClearMYBookOnNoImplied
Parameter.Comment: When set to true this parameter will cause the MY book to be cleared out on receipt of a MO message with a wImpliedSpreadInd equal to a blank. This feature is a failsafe in case CME did not explicitly clear out their implied (MY) books at the end of the previous week.

Parameter.Name: CmeClearMYBookOnMJTypeM
Parameter.Comment: When set to true this parameter will cause the MY book to be cleared out on receipt of a MJ type M (minibatch) message. This feature is a failsafe in case we missed messages or CME did not send them properly.

Parameter.Name: CmePublishMALevelOneAsQuote
Parameter.Comment: When set to true (this has been the current and past behavior) this parameter will cause the top of the MA book to be published as an explicit quote. Some customers are not interested in this value and instead consider the top of the merged MA/MY book as the top of the book.

Parameter.Name: CmeUseLevelBasedDeletes
Parameter.Comment: When set to true will apply new orderbook code to better represent the explict by Level Orderbook format as sent by the CME.

Parameter.Name: CmeEnhancementVersion
Parameter.Comment: Should be set to 1 to alter the feed to make use of the Globex Message enhancements

Parameter.Name: CmeIsMergeVersion
Parameter.Comment: This parameter have to be set to 'True' for CME and CBOT Merge Version. Meanwhile, it has to be used with another previous parameter: CmeEnhancementVersion (set to 1 or larger). Also, CmeIsMergeVersion has to be set to 'true' for the other two parameters followed

Parameter.Name: CmeConvertFractionalPricing
Parameter.Comment: Using Fractional pricing for cbot product, if set to true, the price for cbot product will be displayed as fractional format

Parameter.Name: CmeUseFullDigitsFractionalPricing
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the fractional price for quarter tickers (1/4 or 32nd1/4) will show full digits, e.g. for 1/4 ticker: 105.2 -- 105.25, and for 32nd1/4 ticker: 105.007 -- 105.0075. Noted: Cme assumes that the last digit(5) for quarter tickers is implied

Parameter.Name: CmeIncludeExchangeCodeInSymbol
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to true, the symbol will look like ABC.XCBT or ABC.XCME. Also, by setting this parameter true, a user can have more control on the data from different exchanges by configuring the productdef.xml; if it is set to false, the symbol will only contain the base_symbol, i.e. ABC, IBM, but the exchange code will be published in the field of 'wPartId'

Parameter.Name: CmePublishGlobexPrices
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to true, the price for both cme and cbot product will be displayed as CME Globex Price format

Parameter.Name: UseRecordHandlerStrategy
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to true the feedhandler will enable the commmon module use to process strategies.

Parameter.Name: CmeProcessMOMsgSpreadData
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to true the feedhandler will process spread data contained in MO messages.

Parameter.Name: CmePublishFlatLegFields
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to true the feedhandler will publish flat leg fields for strategies such as wPriceLeg1, wPriceLeg2, etc. When using RecordHandlerStrategy functionality it may be desirable to turn off publishing of these fields.

Parameter.Name: WeeklyOptionRegExps
Parameter.Comment: Pattern for matching weekly expiring mid curve option symbols e.g. E05U5

Parameter.Name: MonthlyOptionRegExps
Parameter.Comment: Pattern for matching monthly expiring mid curve option symbols e.g. GEH5 GE2H5

Parameter.Name: CmeFXMarketSpaceActivationCode
Parameter.Value: Contact Wombat Support to request your activation code for CME/Reuters FXMarketSpace features.

Parameter.Name: CmeFXMarketSpaceActivationCode
Parameter.Value: Contact Wombat Support to request your activation code for CME/Reuters FXMarketSpace features.
